20 A Concurrent Resolution honoring the 50th anniversary
of the Fall of Saigon and end of the Vietnam War;
21 recognizing the subsequent growth of the Vietnamese
American community, culture, and economic impact in
22 Oklahoma; and celebrating those who fought for the
freedom of Vietnam and Vietnamese American citizens.
23
24
ENGR. H. C. R. NO. 1016 Page 1

1 WHEREAS, April 30, 2025, marks the 50th anniversary of the Fall
2 of Saigon, a pivotal moment in world history which marked the end of
3 the Vietnam War and led to mass displacement of millions of
4 Vietnamese refugees; and
5 WHEREAS, many Vietnamese families fled their homeland in search
6 of freedom, safety, and opportunity, enduring perilous journeys and
7 resettling in countries around the world, including the United
8 States; and
9 WHEREAS, the State of Oklahoma became home to a vibrant
10 Vietnamese American community that has enriched the state's
11 cultural, economic, and social landscape over the past five decades;
12 and
13 WHEREAS, the Vietnamese American community in Oklahoma,
14 particularly centered in the Asian District of Oklahoma City and
15 across the state, has demonstrated exceptional resilience, work
16 ethic, and civic commitment; and
17 WHEREAS, Vietnamese Americans in Oklahoma have made lasting
18 contributions as entrepreneurs, educators, medical professionals,
19 public servants, faith leaders, and community advocates; and
20 WHEREAS, cultural celebrations such as Tet (Vietnamese Lunar New
21 Year) and the preservation of Vietnamese heritage have strengthened
22 Oklahoma's multicultural identity and promoted cross-cultural
23 understanding; and
24
