1 WHEREAS, this 50th anniversary provides an opportunity for all
2 Oklahomans to reflect on the tragic costs of war, the power of
3 perseverance, and the enduring values of freedom and democracy; and
4 WHEREAS, in honoring and recognizing our Vietnamese American
5 Community, the State of Oklahoma continues to recognize the South
6 Republic Heritage flag (yellow flag with three red stripes) as the
7 official flag to honor those who have fought for the freedom of
8 Vietnam and our fellow Vietnamese American citizens of the State of
9 Oklahoma; and
10 WHEREAS, the 50th anniversary provides an opportunity for all
11 Oklahomans to reflect on the tragic costs of war, the power of
12 perseverance, and the enduring values of freedom and democracy; and
13 achievements, and sacrifices of Vietnamese Americans in Oklahoma,
14 who have become an integral part of this state's story.
15 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
16 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE, THE SENATE
17 CONCURRING THEREIN:
18 THAT pursuant to the motion of Representative Andy Fugate the
19 Oklahoma State Legislature extends to the Vietnamese American
20 Community sincere gratitude and directs this motion to be presented.
